          "description": "Columbia University hospital cares more about profits than patient care. We had to wait over and hour just to get discharged as the travel nurses and cardiologist dont know how to communicate. A simple discharge order took an hour. Don't come here while nurses are being treated like subhumans as you get terrible care.\n\nEdit: we actually had to wait 2 hours just to he discharged . Even worse, the PA and the fellow both gave different information. They didnt even inform us that the reason my father-in-law had to stay overnight was because the fellow induced a mechanical arrhythmia, while doing cathertization. Completely irresponsible, they didnt even say he had an arrhythmia. Im lucky I have some medical knowledge but I wouldn't send my dog to this hospital, they would discharge him with cat medication and follow up asking about my frog.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205WGFXNW9WVkU0U0RORWRuZHdUMVpyTkhWUGQwRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x27bff071752b797d!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm9XaW5oVVE4SDNEdndwT1ZrNHVPd0E%7C%7C?hl=en",
